description: Grant Morrison continues his earth-shattering run on the Batman titles with this exciting, new ongoing series! Featuring; Art by the remarkable Yanick Paquette (SEVEN SOLDIERS: BULLETEER), BATMAN, INC. marks the next stage of evolution for The Dark Knight. This can't-miss series will star not just Bruce Wayne as Batman, but also a huge number of guest-stars! Don't miss out on this all-new start to a stunning direction for Batman!
name: Mr. Unknown is Dead

Welcome back Tony Daniel as regular writer/artist on BATMAN!

Bruce Wayne may have returned, but when an aging but wealthy technology developer comes to Gotham with his beautiful daughter, it turns out he's in search of a joint project with WayneTech. DNA tracking is the name of his game, and there are others interested in his proposal. But when the developer goes missing, Batman finds that his tracks stop in the city's violent Chinatown neighborhood, where a new deadly Triad gang has taken root. Guest-starring I-Ching!
name: Eye of the Beholder, Part One: Hear No Evil

description:
With Bruce Wayne soon to return to Gotham City, the secret past lives of his parents Thomas and Martha have come back to haunt the family legacy! What bizarre experience in their past is connected to the horrible plan that Tommy Elliot has set in motion? Find out here in part 2 of the 5-part sequel to the best-selling "Heart of Hush"!

Plus, don't miss the start of a new Ragman co- feature, written by Fabian Nicieza (RED ROBIN)! This 5-part story finds Rory Regan starting a new job at the city morgue as his tenement neighborhood is threatened by the Mayor's "renewal plan" and Firefly, an arsonist who might be on the city payroll!
name: The House of Hush, Chapter Two: Reunions; Ashes To Ashes, Part One: Smoldering Embers

description: BRIGHTEST DAY blazes on as the New Guardians seeking the Indigo Entity are shocked to discover a sedated Black Hand. Can Hal Jordan trust the Indigo Tribe to house the herald of Nekron?
name: Lorek Tarr Lok

description: Zatanna just doesn't like L.A. Never did, never will. Attending the opening of Hollywood's new Magic Museum, filled with artifacts and costumes from the world's greatest sorcerers, is more of a chore than a vacation. But she'll be surprised by what she finds there – both a connection to her father, and a truly bizarre threat that she never saw coming! They say the clothes don't make the man… but what happens when the clothes have other ideas? It's one of Zatanna's weirdest adventures yet, in a done-in-one by Adam Beechen (BATMAN BEYOND)!
name: Shades

description: Don't miss the hottest event in comics as BRIGHTEST DAY continues with the search for a new White Lantern. And Martian Manhunter returns to Mars as we discover the origin of the creature mysteriously stalking him. Plus, the evil within Firestorm now haunts Professor Stein! And Hawkman: betrayed!
name: Acrobats

description:
This issue contains the following stories:

  • I Went to My Own Funeral
    Both Gertrude and Basil Jethro were famous surgeons... their skill was the crucial element necessary to the success of a fantastic experiment. For Gertrude was anxious to destroy her insane mate. And live to boast secretly...
  • Three Way Vendetta
  • Bury Me Deep
  • Payment on Time!
    When old Doctor Lester was forced to operate on one of the murderous stowaways, he made careful arrangements for Payment on Time!
  • High Tension
    Up on the towering trapeze wires, under the big circus tent, Alfredo Tarbello vowed to kill the man who threatened his happiness. It would be sublimely simple, htis murder committed under High Tension!
  • Murder on Time!
  • Big Money Man!
    The bank robbery Byron Benson planned would prove to the world that he had become a Big Money Man!
